messages.content:
I need help with a very important assignment for university. The module is called "Computing in Society" and this will account for half of the grade. You also need to understand I only have 5 days to complete it. This is the brief: Generative AI seems poised to change not just business, politics and science but every
aspect of society from communications media and creative arts to personal relationships.
While Generative AI may be the main AI topic of current interest, the project title is the
broader one of AI, and students are free to choose any relevant topic within that general
area.
This project should focus on a particular topic – e.g. Gen AI and the law profession or Gen AI
and visual media or AI and transport or AI and personal relationships or Gen AI and politics
etc. whatever topic that appeals to you - and should research, analyse and discuss the topic
with respect to the future of society. It may be of interest to students to focus on AI/Gen AI
and a future career or AI/Gen AI and an aspect of society that is of particular interest.
Students are expected to produce an original contribution that addresses or illustrates some
aspect of the chosen topic.
Note there is a huge range of topics from the trivial to the profound that relate to the impact
of AI on society – you are expected to avoid the trivial. Keep in mind that I also have to create an 'original contribution'. This might be:
 experiments and comparisons involving Gen AI;
 design of a novel app related to the topic;
 development of an information campaign related to the chosen topic;
 in-depth novel analysis as might be basis for publishable article on a relevant topic;
 an outline for a novel legal/political/ethical framework related to the topic;
 creation of a website supporting some aspect of the chosen topic;
 development of idea for a tech-supported community activity related to the topic;
 outline script for a piece of art/media relevant to the project topic, for example
o a screen play for a short film;
o an educational podcast/video;
o a relevant drama/short story;
... or anything you can convince me is a relevant contribution! / Currently, I am torn between two topics: GenAI and Identity, focusing on impacts on both Self-perception and interpersonal relationships and GenAI and Universal Basic Income, focusing on why UBI is relevant to the AI era and how AI can facilitate its implementation. Considering all the information I have given about the assignment I need you to be really honest and pragmatic and tell me which topic would be better to pursue considering everything. Be warned, I want a real answer not anything along the lines of 'the better choice comes down to you...'
